===============================================================
 PREFLIGHT
===============================================================

[1] Is this a real GPU or a virtualised slice, and do we get
    utilisation readings at all?

    name, memory.total [MiB], utilization.gpu [%], driver_version
    NVIDIA GeForce RTX 4090, 49140 MiB, 0 %, 580.105.08

    OK   utilization.gpu is readable

    processes currently on this GPU:
      pid, used_gpu_memory [MiB]
    (if you see PIDs that are not yours, utilisation is shared and
     nvidia-smi readings will be contaminated by another tenant)

[2] Does the CUDA / torch / vLLM stack actually line up?

    preflight.sh: line 40: python3: command not found


    NOTE: vLLM wheels are built against specific torch+CUDA pairs.
    torch 2.12 / CUDA 13 is very new.  If 'pip install vllm' pulls a
    wheel that then fails to import, the fix is to pin an older torch
    in a venv rather than to fight the system one:
      python3 -m venv ~/autodl-tmp/venv && source ~/autodl-tmp/venv/bin/activate
      pip install vllm            # let it choose its own torch

[3] Disk.  Weights are the big item; put them on the data disk.

    Filesystem      Size  Used Avail Use% Mounted on
    overlay          30G   53M   30G   1% /
    /dev/md0         50G  1.6M   50G   1% /root/autodl-tmp

    A 14B model in bf16 is ~28 GB.  The 30 GB system disk will NOT
    hold it.  Everything must go to /root/autodl-tmp.

===============================================================
 VERDICT
===============================================================
  VRAM 49140 MiB  -> run Qwen2.5-14B-Instruct (better than 7B:
                       closer to what agentic serving actually uses)
  GPU util readable -> V2 can use nvidia-smi AND vLLM metrics

  Next:  bash setup_autodl.sh
